Vin Diesel gets choked up talking about Paul Walker before an advanced screening of Furious 7 in Los Angeles.The actor was visibly emotional during his speech to introduce the latest entry in the Universal franchise, recounting memories of his late co-star. In some ways, this was the hardest movie I ve ever had to do, Diesel said. The relationships you see in the film are so real. When the tragedy happened I lost my friend. I lost my brother. Diesel added that he hoped the fans enjoyed the film, as it was made with them in mind. More importantly, it s for my brother there, Diesel said, pointing to the image of Walker on the big screen.